    :shortdes: Invisible Fence
    :tags: Language

.<a href="#post-202">#202</a> reminded me that the phrase
“<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Invisible_Fence_Inc.">Invisible Fence</a>”
is a huge pet peeve of mine.
It's very close to two words, two lies:
there's not a fence that's invisible, there's no fence at all!
And if there's no fence, it can't be invisible either:
you can only meaningfully call something “invisible”
if it's actually <em>there</em> but just can't be seen.


